#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
validate-schema — Script 3 of 5: Validate structured data files against
schema definitions BEFORE data enters canvas authoring.

Google SRE pattern: validates data at ingestion time, not mid-canvas.
Catches schema violations early — prevents bad data from propagating
into canvas authoring and contaminating downstream analysis.

Usage:
    ./validate-schema DATA_TYPE FILE_PATH [--schema-dir PATH] [--dry-run]

DATA_TYPE is one of: competitor-profile, review-corpus, market-sizing,
                     canvas-frontmatter

Exit codes:
    0  PASS                 All checks passed, no issues.
    1  FAIL                 Blocking violations found (required missing,
                            type mismatch, enum, range, format, or custom rule
                            ERROR).
    2  PASS_WITH_WARNINGS   Non-blocking issues found (optional missing,
                            warnings, custom rule WARNING).
    3  INTERNAL_ERROR       Script bug, corrupted schema/data YAML, or
                            missing dependency. Escalate to Wesley.
    4  INVALID_INPUT        Invalid arguments, unknown data type, or file
                            not found. Fix inputs and re-run.

Output: Structured JSON to stdout. Human-readable logs to stderr.
"""

